Ahead of their @PlatformPresents #PoetryGala tonight at the @savoythetreldn for this episode of #sisterhoodworkspodcast I talked to the fabulous co-founders  @galagordon and @isabellamacpherson about creating space for rising talent and female voices, what it takes to make a creativebusiness work, and the power of two.... #AllBright #SisterhoodWorksPodcast #powerduo #breakaleg

Download the latest episode of the Sisterhood Works Podcast for our most candid conversation yet. @DebbieWosskow chats to AllBright aesthetician and A-List facialist, @georgialouisesk about declaring bankruptcy in her 20s, and creating the sisterhood she needed to help rebuild her business into a globally successful brand. I will be in conversation in person with @georgialouisesk on Wednesday about her role as a @lamer ambassador. Can’t wait!  #AllBright #SisterhoodWorksPodcast

Issue four of AllBright magazine is out. New Year inspiration abounds with features, stories and advice to make 2020 The Year of Your Best Self. Whether it’s a change in career path,  the motivation to continue building your dream, or the inspiration to dedicate more time to ‘project you’, this issue has everything you need to make this year your best yet. Delighted to have the icon that is @therealdvf gracing the cover and telling us inside how she built her empire. Pick up your copy next time you’re #intheclub, or read it online at www.allbrightcollective.com/magazine  #AllBright #AllBrightMagazine.

It was an absolute privilege and delight today to receive an honorary degree of Doctor of Science, by Royal Holloway, University of London @royalholloway . It feels particularly special to be granted the award by an institution invested in and built on the education of women. #sisterhoodworks #lifelonglearning #royalholloway

Listen to Episode 3 of the #SisterhoodWorksPodcast now. It was a pleasure to talk all things Sisterhood with the sister power duo  @ashleyrachel and @soothingsista at #TheAllBrightWestHollywood. I loved hearing about building social media powers brand, what empowering other women means to them and what it’s like working with family. #AllBright #SisterhoodWorksPodcast #sisterhoodworks

Every 10 seconds somewhere in the world, a young girl is mutilated. This devastating statistic is preventing millions of girls and women from reaching their potential. It has to change. As an @unwomenuk ambassador I am extremely proud to support this important campaign -  #drawaline to end violence against women and girls. #endfgm

What an honour to speak with the incredible @realkellyholmes1500 for Episode 2 of the #SisterhoodWorksPodcast. Dame Kelly speaks candidly about her fear around her career change, overcoming mental health challenges, and how you can harness your strengths and pursue your dreams.#allbright #SisterhoodWorksPodcast #SisterhoodWorks #inspiration

Episode 1 of the #SisterhoodWorksPodcast I/@DebbieWosskow chats to @KateMosseWriter about the entrepreneurial side of being a successful writer, advice for other aspiring women writers, and what Sisterhood means to her. #AllBright #SisterhoodWorksPodcast #SisterhoodWorks

@debbiewosskow and I are excited to announce that our brand new podcast ‘Sisterhood Works’ is here. We’ve been collecting stories from women who inspire us, finding out how they became the successes they are today, understanding the challenges they had to overcome and hearing their practical tips on how we can all make a mark. We’ve chatted to a host of amazing women - all in celebration of the power of sisterhood. Hope you enjoy! Available to listen and download on Spotify here: https://open.spotify.com/show/1RPukFx7wZiO99Lp55rxuI

My opinion piece in @financialtimes today on equality and confidence. Among all the disparities between men and women in the workplace, be it between levels of pay, positions of executive authority or governance roles at board level, the common factor running through them is a disparity in confidence.  There are practical things we can all do to bridge the gap, but confidence-building is a life long mission, so it’s never too soon to start. #sisterhoodworks #allbright #confidence

Flashback to last week when @allbright landed in #hongkong for the launch of Connect and @allbrightacademy. With so much going on in Hong Kong at the moment it was wonderful to see so many incredible women coming together to inspire, support and network with each other. When women come together amazing things happen. #sisterhoodworks #lifelonglearning #inspiration

Whilst we’ve been busy talking #equalpayday here in the UK my awesome co-founder @debbiewosskow and head of partnerships @nickisingh have been in Sydney launching the @allbrightacademy and @allbright Connect in Sydney. This is the next step in building our global sisterhood and it’s fantastic to see so many awesome women out in force to support. #sisterhoodworks #allbright #allbrightacademy #teamworkmakesthedreamwork

Talking gender pay gap on the BBC tonight to mark equal pay day. For every pound a man earns a woman earns 82 pence. The pay equality act came out in the 1970’s!! and despite the fact this issue has hit the headlines for the last few years progress is painfully slow. The @fawcettsociety says there won’t be parity until 2080 at the current rate of improvement. @allbrightacademy free courses have a negotiation module that offers guidance on how to have the pay conversation at work. #timetolisten #genderpaygap #allbright #equality

Celebrating the awesome talent of @brigetteromanek in @archdigest talking @allbright #westhollywood design. Brigette has it all - talent, personality and an instinctive understanding of the needs of our growing global sisterhood. #creativetalent #interiordesign #sisterhoodworks #allbright

Talking about all things @allbright levelling the playing field for women on page 3 of today’s Times. Our spaces - physical and digital - are here to celebrate and champion women and I feel lucky every day to be surrounded by so many incredible women and enlightened men driving this change. #mondaymotivation #sisterhoodworks #teamwork

Last night we celebrated with international young leaders as part of the 10th Annual @oneyoungworld Summit, at The AllBright Mayfair. @allbright proudly champions the future of female leaders and entrepreneurs, and the impact that empowered entrepreneurship can have on social change. We were joined by three fantastic women from our Sisterhood, @im_ohne , @justwearshq and @byrotationofficial, to help inspire the next generation of international leaders. Championed by leaders and activists including @sussexroyal , @justinptrudeau and @elliegoulding, it’s an honour for AllBright to celebrate and support this new generation of bright young talent. 
#allbright #oyw2019 #buildingabetterworld #leadership

Issue 3 of @allbright magazine! This issue is a celebration of all things #sustainable to coincide with our #allgreen week of events. The issues facing our planet are immense and it can make us feel overwhelmed and unsure of what we can do to help. There are no easy answers and we are all learning. Our aim with AllGreen and this issue is to showcase the people leading the charge for change and to outline the practical and sometimes small things we can all do to live more sustainably. We are thrilled to have our friend and @allbright member @naomieharris on the cover and talking about green living inside. #sisterhoodworks #sustainability

First Look at @allbright West Hollywood in The Hollywood Reporter today! Designed by @brigetteromanek and with art curated by @bethgreenacre_london , we are thrilled to share the space with our growing #losangeles sisterhood…and cannot wait to celebrate with everyone tomorrow night!  #seeyouintheclub #sisterhoodworks

Another amazing soirée @toryburch last night to celebrate and discuss the power of unconventional thinking. I was in conversation with one of my oldest friends and @allbright art curator @bethgreenacre_london and one of my newest friends and member @lifecoachblades . Lynne talked about facing your fears and having the courage to stray outside of the lines. To care a bit less about what others think and to trust our intuition. Beth asked us to think more creatively by looking all around for inspiration, at people and things and even in dark corners. All can help us be more creative. We left feeling uplifted and empowered, not to mention wearing kick-ass shoes and for me the most incredible collar I’ve seen on a dress!

It was a pleasure to host our @allbrightacademy breakfast today to launch our latest course for Freelancers and Consultants. We heard some wise advice and practical solutions from @mother_pukka and @kittysaxton on everything from flexible working and why it is still misunderstood by most organisations to looking within to set our own boundaries and being honest about what we really want for our careers. #projectyou is still something not many of us spend  enough time on as we focus so much energy on every thing and every one else. Book time in for yourself. You are your most important project. #sisterhoodworks
